Nigeria’s number one man, President Muhammadu Buhari has joined family and friends of Babatunde Ogunnaike, a professor of more than 25 years and Dean of Engineering at Delaware University, in mourning the departure of the scholar and administrator.  The president, in a statement Tuesday by his spokesman, Femi Adesina, said Ogunnaike who contributed “significantly” to the lines of the National Anthem showed his patriotism and dedication to the wellbeing of the nation in the living words that daily reinforced the faith and spirit of Nigerians.He said the long hours of research, spanning into years, enhanced knowledge and understanding, and prepared generations for greater works.He prayed that the Almighty God receive the soul of Prof. Ogunnaike and comfort his family.  source Prof. Babatunde Ogunnaike, one of the five authors of Nigeria’s national anthem is dead.The Ijebu Igbo, Ogun State indigene passed on at the age of 65. Educationist and publisher Gbenro Adegbola confirmed his death on Tuesday, The Nation reports.Other co-authors of the anthem were John Ilechukwu, Eme Etim Akpan, Sota… In "News" By Diana Omueza   Abuja   -     Mrs Bisayo Busari-Akinnadeju, Founder, Project One, Civil Society Organisation (CSO), says the organisation will award scholarships to students in recognition of the composers of Nigerian National Anthem. Busari-Akinnadeju restated in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Abuja… In "News" Nigerian Grammy-nominated artiste, Damini Ogulu also known as Burna Boy has disclosed that sitting for interviews makes him very uncomfortable more than going on a tour. The singer made this known in an interview with Nigerian-American entertainment journalist Lola Ogunnaike, where she sheds new light on the often reserved artist,… In "Entertainment"